 He followed this with St. Elsewhere and Miami Vice before making his feature film debut with Hoosiers. His additional screen credits include Fresh Horses, Rudy, Moonlight and Valentino, and The Game of Their Lives.\n\nAn upcoming move is being made called Little Red Wagon which will come out in 2011.  Anspaugh was married to actress Roma Downey from 1995 to 1998. The couple have a daughter, Reilly Marie.\n\nDescription above from the Wikipedia article David Anspaugh, licensed under CC-BY-SA, full list of contributors on Wikipedia.','1946-09-24',NULL),(2932,'Sam Macaroni',NULL,'',NULL,NULL),(2933,'Keitaro Motonaga',NULL,'Keitaro Motonaga is a Japanese animation director.',NULL,NULL),(2934,'Scott Derrickson','Denver, Colorado, USA','Scott Derrickson is an American filmmaker who is known for directing horror films such as Deliver Us from Evil, Hellraiser: Inferno, Sinister and The Black Phone. He also directed the superhero film Doctor Strange starring Benedict Cumberbatch. In March 2022, Derrickson was set to direct The Gorge for Skydance. Apple TV+ acquried the right of the film.','1966-07-16',NULL),(2935,'Vicente Amorim','Vienne, Autriche','','1966-01-01',NULL),(2936,'Anthony O\'Brien',NULL,'',NULL,NULL),(2937,'Yuan Tao',NULL,'',NULL,NULL),(2938,'Lluís Quílez','Barcelona, Spain','','1978-12-08',NULL),(2939,'Kristen Coury',NULL,'',NULL,NULL),(2940,'Charles Guard','England, UK','','1975-12-19',NULL),(2941,'Peter Atencio','Ft. Collins, Colorado, USA','','1983-03-15',NULL),(2942,'Paul Guilfoyle','Jersey City, New Jersey, USA','From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia\n\nPaul Guilfoyle (July 14, 1902 – June 27, 1961) was an American stage, film and television actor. Later in his career, he also directed films and television episodes.\n\nGuilfoyle was born in Jersey City, New Jersey.\n\nHe started off working on stage, performing on Broadway in 16 plays according to the Internet Broadway Database, beginning with The Jolly Roger and Cyrano de Bergerac in 1923 and ending with